{
  "analysis": "The current `/app/gpt2.c` compiles and runs but produces degenerate output because BPE never merges. Panel 2 identified the key bug: `rank()` searches for concatenated token strings (`token1token2`), but `vocab.bpe` stores merges as `token1 token2` with a space separator, so no rank is ever found. Base tokens 0-255 are already canonical GPT-2 byte-to-unicode strings. The forward pass and logits are present and use correct embedding-row indexing. I will make a minimal patch to `enc()` so it looks up the pair with a space separator, then verify tokenization with a probe and run inference.",
  "plan": "Patch `/app/gpt2.c` `enc()` to build `mp` as `p[i] + ' ' + p[i+1]` for rank lookup, while still merging as `p[i] + p[i+1]`. Compile with `gcc -O3 /app/gpt2.c -o /app/a.out -lm`. Run a compact tokenizer probe to confirm `The` -> expected GPT-2 IDs and merges happen. Then run `/app/a.out` with the required interface to verify non-degenerate output.",
